"Hopbursting-sounded alluring!  So the usually cool Stone Brewing bottle.  Pours a slightly cloudy yellow with a medium white head that has decent retention.  Nice foamy lace down the glass.  Nose is bitter and acidic.  No discernable malt character.  Mouthfeel is medium which is surprising given the thin appearance.  Taste is just a slight malt character followed by big citrus and pine hits.  Moderately bitter but finishes clean.  The second bottle was better.  Perfect for a hot summer day.  Let your friends quaff bud light while you enjoy big hop in a little beer!"
