"Final Word: Appropriately named, as this beer’s claim to fame is how drinkable it is; it’s a great beer to keep a sixer of in your fridge for warm weather drinking. The hop forward profile gives you a big, juicy, citrusy hop punch right up front, but with an almost completely clean finish. Speaking of the finish, that’s my only complaint with this beer; it cleans up so well that you actually miss the flavors that could be there. I don’t mind a clean finish per se, but the finish here sees the flavors completely disappearing, which makes it extremely drinkable and light feeling, but condemns it to only being a beer suitable for drinking while you’re out grilling in the sun. Pick some up if that’s the case, but outside of the aforementioned sun-baked-patio scenario, most drinkers seeking an IPA will want something more complex and robust."
