"Overall I thought this was a nice beer and I thought it was nice example of a session IPA, but I felt like the green onion hop profile held it back from being as good as it could be and those green onion flavors kind of clashed with the tropical fruit hop flavors. This beer had nice drinkability, it was smooth, clean, very crisp, not too filling, and the taste didn't do the best job at holding my attention and I think the carbonation might wear on me. It's smooth enough for a session IPA, but the flavors don't hold my attention like others in the style, so one or two would be my limit. What I like the most about this beer was the tropical fruit hop aspect and the appearance I thought they were both pretty good and the highlights of this beer. What I liked the least about this beer was the green onion hop aspect, it just isn't for me and I think it clashed with the other hop flavors. I don't think I would get this beer again, I think I would buy some All Day IPA instead. I might recommend this to people who like Session IPA's, but I don't think it's a must try. All in all this was a Solid Session IPA, but it had some aspects that held it back from being a great beer and stand out for the style. As it is I think it's falls right in the middle for session IPA's and it's for sure not my favorite Stone beer. Solid job, but I think with a little work this could be a standout for the style, better luck next time guys."
