"Poured from a bottle into a shaker pint, the beer is a golden-lemon coloring with a thin, low profile, clingy, white head. Aromas of tart lemon and grapefruit, rich resinous pine pitch notes, and a subtle candy sweetness. Flavors are a blast of lemon sweet and tart, pepper spice, and pine pitch forward, with a more subtle blending of citrus fruits as the beer crosses the palate. Crisp and effervescent throughout, keeping the beer extremely light and refreshing. A grapefruit bomb by the time you get to the aftertaste, with the pine notes now nothing more than a highlight. Crisp, dry finish. This is a very good beer, and easily drinkable. Bravo!"
