"Crystal clear yellow body beneath a small, sticky white head. Pungent ruby red grapefruit, peach, mango, and resinous pine aromatics. Super hoppy, chuggable, refreshing flavor. Dank, oily hop resins, zesty citrus, herbs, miscellaneous tropical fruits. Pretty much nothing in the malt department. Light bodied, bitter, and crisp. Lots of great hop character in a light, easy-drinking format...what's not to like? My only wish is that this was priced more like DayTime, which is a more reasonable $8 a sixer for your sessioning pleasure."
"O - 4.25 - This is a great session IPA. It's still a hop bomb @ 4.5%"
"O: There's some great hop aroma and flavor to be had here, and true to its style it will sit lightly in the stomach and not throw you for a loop after a few pints. However, like most other session IPAs I've had, the lack of malt body really detracts from the drinkability. It feels too watery and the hop astringencies build to borderline unpleasant levels. In all fairness these are the same criticisms I've had of the vast majority of session IPAs I've tried to date. If you are a fan of the style, this will probably hit the spot for you."
