"i am personally a fan of the session ipa style, since it is conducive to the starting early-going all night approach i favor when imbibing. that said, i find the Go To IPA a worthy addition to the category, and one that i hope will become as ubiquitous as their flagship india pale. color and appearance are more like the 'fizzy yellow' brews Stone rallies against. minimal lacing left on the sides of my pint, but i'm not drinking this through my eyes. aroma delivers a fragrant burst of ruby grapefruit, tangerine, and some herbal sage. while the mouthfeel is on the thin side (no surprises there), the bitterness makes up for that aspect, lingering on the sides and back of the tongue pleasantly. carbonation is medium, making for a most refreshing sessioner. i will add this one to my list of regular purchases."
